de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.syntax

Class SynArgMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.syntax.SynArgMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<SynArgMap>

    public class SynArgMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<SynArgMap>
    The SynArgMap is a class representing the relationship that maps various SyntacticArgument instances of the same SubcategorizationFrameSet instance.
    Therefore, every SynArgMap instance contains exactly two syntactic arguments which are in a relationship.
    Author:
    Silvana Hartmann, Zijad Maksuti

      • getArg1

        public SyntacticArgument getArg1()
        Returns the first of two SyntacticArgument instances which are in a relationship represented by this SynArgMap instance.
        Returns:
        the first of two syntactic arguments in a relationship or null if the first argument is not set.

        Note that UBY-LMF requires that every SynArgMap instance always has both syntacti arguments set. Absence of one of these arguments may indicate to incomplete conversion of the original resource.

        See Also:
        getArg2()
